            <p facs="#facs_52_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>cʼest
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>-521
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>is different—if it is changing, aséehics are changing, as everything changing, when it is
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>different—but in the moment in which in these changing contents you ACCEPT something, then it is
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>UNconditional. Here I want to say a word against naturalistic attempt, generally, to arrive
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>the moral imperative. I have already accepted all the relative possible—and this is not a point of
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_52_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>discussion, with the naturalists—but the point of DISCussION with them is the conconditional character.
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>take a naturalist who vonies, unconditional character of the ernical imperative,WHATEVER THE
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>CONTENT May BE. In which attitude does he deny this? In the attitude of the Echolar, the philosopher
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>or scientist, who seems for truth and who secks HONESTLy for truth. Tell one of these naturalists
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>that he will get a higher pay—if such a thing every would happen!—if he DENIES his naturalism.
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>Then the following happens: the tempation is certainly there; he would know that from the moment
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>on in which he would change his esthical theory for the sake of a better social position, he would deny
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>what is usually called his integrity, he would give up his honesty. That means: in ;maintaining his
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>te
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>naturalistic relativism, he applies the absolute detegorical imperatives of honesty and integrity.
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>If he TOESN'T—which is quite possible—he would destroy himself because from this moment on,
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_52_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>he would say what he says with bad conscience, and on this basis his self-affirmation as personality
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>would go to pieces. There are of course many escape-mechanisms, compromises, rationalisations¬
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>I don’t need to go into that now. But THEY dieY ONLy NECESSusY because the fundamenta¬
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>principle is valid, otherwise no escape-mechanism would be used at all, if we make such a decision.
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>So the honest naturalist, who is willing to become a martyr in an extreme situation, for his relativistic
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>dʼune manière vie de lʼannée
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>cʼest en
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>toutes les
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_12" n="N012"/>de mon ami
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_13" n="N013"/>dʼavoir lʼautre
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_14" n="N014"/>M r de
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_15" n="N015"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_16" n="N016"/>dʼune manière est
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_17" n="N017"/>Pour Vous
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_18" n="N018"/>Votre
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_19" n="N019"/>décrier de
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_20" n="N020"/>dʼavoir lʼautre vieuse
               <lb facs="#facs_52_tr_2_tl_21" n="N021"/>des
            </p>
            
